all the juniors, including your brother.


739
0:54:48,109 --> 0:54:49,677
That's all lies.


740
0:54:49,677 --> 0:54:52,18
You spent your whole time
writing obscene poetry.


741
0:54:52,18 --> 0:54:53,782
My poems aren't obscene.


742
0:54:53,782 --> 0:54:56,785
They're in the manner of Wilde.
That's filthy enough for me.


743
0:54:56,785 --> 0:54:59,421
Have you ever actually read
any of Oscar's poems?


744
0:54:59,421 --> 0:55:3,458
I wouldn't sully my mind
with perverted trash like that.


745
0:55:3,458 --> 0:55:5,46
Tell him to pick his feet up!


746
0:55:5,46 --> 0:55:7,662
He's not straight!


747
0:55:7,662 --> 0:55:9,998
Are you calling Oscar a pervert?


748
0:55:9,998 --> 0:55:11,566
Because that's libelous.


749
0:55:11,566 --> 0:55:15,69
I'm not saying he is one.
I'm saying he's posing as one...


750
0:55:15,69 --> 0:55:17,439
which is worse.


751
0:55:17,439 --> 0:55:19,474
His wife's divorcing him.


752
0:55:19,474 --> 0:55:23,378
Did you know that?
For sodomy!


753
0:55:23,378 --> 0:55:26,381
- That's completely untrue!
- I hope it is.


754
0:55:26,381 --> 0:55:32,821
Because if it were true,
I'd shoot him on sight.


755
0:55:32,821 --> 0:55:38,76
You will cease to see Wilde,
or I'll cut you off without a penny.


756
0:55:38,76 --> 0:55:40,929
As though I wanted your money...


757
0:55:40,929 --> 0:55:44,265
what little you have left
from your tarts.


758
0:55:44,265 --> 0:55:47,368
How dare you speak
to your father like that.


759
0:55:47,368 --> 0:55:51,272
What a funny little man you are.


760
0:55:51,272 --> 0:55:54,375
Come back here,
you filthy-minded sissy!


761
0:55:54,375 --> 0:55:56,11
You're absurd!


762
0:55:56,11 --> 0:55:58,913
And you're nothing but a bum-boy!


763
0:55:58,913 --> 0:56:4,352
You're pathetic!


764
0:56:4,352 --> 0:56:6,688
I'm a bloody good shot.
Better than he is.


765
0:56:6,688 --> 0:56:8,923
I'll shoot him through the heart
if he threatens me.


766
0:56:8,923 --> 0:56:11,226
Hadn't you better use
a silver bullet then?


767
0:56:11,226 --> 0:56:13,228
Here's one for the Black Douglas.


768
0:56:13,228 --> 0:56:15,43
Bosie, for God's sake!


769
0:56:15,43 --> 0:56:17,232
And one for his liver!
One for his lights!


770
0:56:17,232 --> 0:56:23,438
One for his stinking rotten soul!


771
0:56:23,438 --> 0:56:26,274
I'll save one for myself.


772
0:56:26,274 --> 0:56:45,193
My own father...
he wants to kill me.


773
0:56:45,193 --> 0:56:48,997
My life is everything
I ever wanted.


774
0:56:48,997 --> 0:56:52,166
I have fame.


775
0:56:52,166 --> 0:56:54,869
I have recognition.


776
0:56:54,869 --> 0:56:57,972
With two plays
about to open in London...


777
0:56:57,972 --> 0:57:1,175
I may even have money.


778
0:57:1,175 --> 0:57:5,13
The world is at my command...


779
0:57:5,13 --> 0:57:9,551
yet I can't command myself.


780
0:57:9,551 --> 0:57:25,733
I can't command
my feelings for you.


781
0:57:25,733 --> 0:57:28,836
<i>- Thank you.
- Constance, my dear.</i>


782
0:57:28,836 --> 0:57:40,48
How nice.


783
0:57:40,48 --> 0:57:43,451
I brought you your letters.


784
0:57:43,451 --> 0:57:46,721
You haven't been home
for so long.


785
0:57:46,721 --> 0:57:53,127
Thank you.


786
0:57:53,127 --> 0:57:55,797
It's so much more convenient
for Oscar living in the West End...


787
0:57:55,797 --> 0:57:58,66
when he has a play coming on.


788
0:57:58,66 --> 0:58:1,97
I'm like a northern businessman
keeping an eye on his factory.


789
0:58:1,97 --> 0:58:4,305
The boys ask for you
all the time.


790
0:58:4,305 --> 0:58:7,141
They're longing to see you.


791
0:58:7,141 --> 0:58:10,445
Oscar has to make sure
the play's a success, Constance.


792
0:58:10,445 --> 0:58:12,213
I'll come round this afternoon...


793
0:58:12,213 --> 0:58:16,184
for tea.


794
0:58:16,184 --> 0:58:22,757
It's the dress rehearsal
this afternoon.


795
0:58:22,757 --> 0:58:24,726
Tomorrow then.
I'll come tomorrow.


796
0:58:24,726 --> 0:58:34,268
Well, tomorrow then.


797
0:58:34,268 --> 0:58:37,372
Good-bye, my dear.


798
0:58:37,372 --> 0:58:45,647
Good-bye.


799
0:58:45,647 --> 0:58:57,392
Good-bye, Constance.


800
0:58:57,392 --> 0:58:59,861
- Something like that.
- I'm not trying to get anything.


801
0:58:59,861 --> 0:59:3,931
I hope so. It would be rather fun.
Perhaps a codfish.


802
0:59:3,931 --> 0:59:6,901
Codfish. I've a strong feeling
that codfish live rather deeper.


803
0:59:6,901 --> 0:59:13,808
- Do you think we'll have skate...
- Possibly.


804
0:59:13,808 --> 0:59:18,413
I don't think there'll be anything
for our table tonight, my love. No luck.


805
0:59:18,413 --> 0:59:20,782
I think I'd better stay.
You're getting a cold.


806
0:59:20,782 --> 0:59:24,986
No, no. I'm all right.
Let's get the boys some ices.


807
0:59:24,986 --> 0:59:29,323
- Boys, you stay and look after nanny.
- Oh, all right.


808
0:59:29,323 --> 0:59:31,359
We'll look after nanny.


809
0:59:31,359 --> 0:59:35,363
I could take the boys to the dentist
on Thursday on their way back to school.


810
0:59:35,363 --> 0:59:37,365
But the whole point of them
having dentistry now...


811
0:59:37,365 --> 0:59:44,605
is so they can stuff themselves with
sweets for a week before we lose them.


812
0:59:44,605 --> 1:0:9,397
- Are you quite sure?
- Bosie'll look after me.


813
1:0:9,397 --> 1:0:11,365
Get your coat on, quick!


814
1:0:11,365 --> 1:0:15,2
I've got a present for you!


815
1:0:15,2 --> 1:0:17,38
Oh, God.


816
1:0:17,38 --> 1:0:20,408
- You're not still seedy, are you?
- Bosie, where have you been?


817
1:0:20,408 --> 1:0:23,1
I've had no one to talk to,
no one to look after me.


818
1:0:23,1 --> 1:0:26,848
Don't be so pathetic.
I've found you the divinest boy.


819
1:0:26,848 --> 1:0:29,784
- Bosie, you promised Constance...
- Bugger Constance.


820
1:0:29,784 --> 1:0:32,42
I'm not your nanny.
Come on. We're going out.


821
1:0:32,42 --> 1:0:36,491
Bosie, please.


822
1:0:36,491 --> 1:0:40,228
You look such an idiot
lying there. Revolting.


823
1:0:40,228 --> 1:0:42,497
- Have you forgotten how to wash?
- As a matter of fact...


824
1:0:42,497 --> 1:0:46,0
I'm dying for a glass of water.


825
1:0:46,0 --> 1:0:49,537
- You know where the jug is.
- Bosie, darling.


826
1:0:49,537 --> 1:0:53,441
It stinks in here. You'll be wanting me
to empty your chamber pot next.


827
1:0:53,441 --> 1:0:57,545
Well, I emptied your chamber pot.
I looked after you.


828
1:0:57,545 --> 1:0:59,947
Well, I'm not looking after you.
Not now.


829
1:0:59,947 --> 1:1:2,617
You don't interest me.
Not when you're ill.


830
1:1:2,617 --> 1:1:5,419
You're just a boring middle-aged man
with a blocked-up nose.


831
1:1:5,419 --> 1:1:9,657
- Bosie, dearest boy.
- Shut up!


832
1:1:9,657 --> 1:1:13,594
"Dearest boy, darling Bosie."
It doesn't mean anything.


833
1:1:13,594 --> 1:1:16,931
You don't love me. The only person
you've ever loved is yourself.


834
1:1:16,931 --> 1:1:19,233
You like me.
You lust after me.


835
1:1:19,233 --> 1:1:23,971
You go about with me because
I've got a title. That's all.


836
1:1:23,971 --> 1:1:26,407
You like to write about
dukes and duchesses...


837
1:1:26,407 --> 1:1:27,975
but you know nothing about them.


838
1:1:27,975 --> 1:1:29,844
You're the biggest snob
I've ever met...


839
1:1:29,844 --> 1:1:33,247
and you think you're so daring
because you fuck the occasional boy.


840
1:1:33,247 --> 1:1:35,583
Please, you're killing me.


841
1:1:35,583 --> 1:1:37,485
You'll just about do
when you're at your best.


842
1:1:37,485 --> 1:1:41,823
You're amusing... very amusing... but when
you're not at your best, you're no one.


843
1:1:41,823 --> 1:1:46,6
All I asked for
was a glass of water.


844
1:1:46,6 --> 1:1:52,6
For Christ's sake!
There you are then!


845
1:1:52,6 --> 1:2:0,775
Now will you shut up
about the fucking water?


846
1:2:0,775 --> 1:2:2,777
There are two boys
waiting out there.


847
1:2:2,777 --> 1:2:5,79
If you're not coming,
I'll fuck them both myself.


848
1:2:5,79 --> 1:2:9,784
I'll take them to the Grand and
fuck them in front of the whole hotel...


849
1:2:9,784 --> 1:2:27,768
and I'll send you the bill.


850
1:2:27,768 --> 1:2:29,27
Drink this.


851
1:2:29,27 --> 1:2:37,345
- It will help your fever.
- He's ashamed of loving men.


852
1:2:37,345 --> 1:2:40,348
His father bullies him,
his mother spoils him...


853
1:2:40,348 --> 1:2:42,483
and then berates him
for being spoiled.


854
1:2:42,483 --> 1:2:48,689
Neither of them gives him any real love.
They're torturing him.


855
1:2:48,689 --> 1:2:52,426
And what's truly dreadful
is that when...


856
1:2:52,426 --> 1:2:56,23
he can't bear it
and has one of his...


857
1:2:56,23 --> 1:2:58,366
he becomes
exactly like his father.


858
1:2:58,366 --> 1:3:4,38
- And he hates himself for that.
- You're too kind about him.


859
1:3:4,38 --> 1:3:10,177
You can't be too kind about
someone who's been so hurt.


860
1:3:10,177 --> 1:3:16,55
Yet if I go on trying to come
between Bosie and his father...


861
1:3:16,55 --> 1:3:18,252
that'll destroy me.


862
1:3:18,252 --> 1:3:22,623
Bosie's quite capable
of destroying you on his own.


863
1:3:22,623 --> 1:3:25,493
Look how much you wrote
while he was away.


864
1:3:25,493 --> 1:3:28,996
Two wonderful plays
which will run for years.


865
1:3:28,996 --> 1:3:39,974
Back comes Bosie,
and what have you written since?


866
1:3:39,974 --> 1:3:43,844
You know how much I...


867
1:3:43,844 --> 1:3:48,82
Iove and admire you...


868
1:3:48,82 --> 1:3:50,718
but you're throwing
your genius away.


869
1:3:50,718 --> 1:3:54,455
- For what?
- It's highly ironic.


870
1:3:54,455 --> 1:3:58,59
Queensberry thinks Bosie and I
are locked in nightly embrace...


871
1:3:58,59 --> 1:4:4,432
and in reality, we've been
the purest model of Greek love since...


872
1:4:4,432 --> 1:4:9,47
Bosie doesn't like doing it with me,
but I've loved him.


873
1:4:9,47 --> 1:4:14,8
- I've educated him.
- But he's never grown up.


874
1:4:14,8 --> 1:4:17,478
And he never will.


875
1:4:17,478 --> 1:4:20,481
I'm not taking him back, Robbie.


876
1:4:20,481 --> 1:4:24,218
Not again.


877
1:4:24,218 --> 1:4:26,52
I can't.


878
1:4:26,52 --> 1:4:30,858
I've been very foolish,
very fond...


879
1:4:30,858 --> 1:4:33,461
but now I must grow up myself.


880
1:4:33,461 --> 1:4:36,364
Oh, please, don't do that.


881
1:4:36,364 --> 1:4:42,269
You're an artist.
Artists are always children at heart.


882
1:4:42,269 --> 1:4:48,642
Oh, Robbie,
I sometimes I wonder if...


883
1:4:48,642 --> 1:4:56,5
Back page, sir.


884
1:4:56,5 --> 1:4:59,854
My God. Francis Douglas.


885
1:4:59,854 --> 1:5:1,856
- What?
- Bosie's brother.


886
1:5:1,856 --> 1:5:7,228
He's been found shot.
He's dead.


887
1:5:7,228 --> 1:5:12,8
But he's just got engaged.


888
1:5:12,8 --> 1:5:27,214
Poor, poor Bosie.
He'll be utterly distraught.


889
1:5:27,214 --> 1:5:30,317
<i>He killed himself.</i>


890
1:5:30,317 --> 1:5:33,888
It was my father.
He drove him to it.


891
1:5:33,888 --> 1:5:38,826
I'm sure your father's
just as upset as everyone else.


892
1:5:38,826 --> 1:5:43,597
No, he's not.


893
1:5:43,597 --> 1:5:47,301
He says it's a judgment
on Roseberry and my mother...


894
1:5:47,301 --> 1:5:59,28
and me and you.


895
1:5:59,28 --> 1:6:3,284
We've got to stop him, Oscar...


896
1:6:3,284 --> 1:6:9,29
before he drives
my whole family to suicide.


897
1:6:9,29 --> 1:6:12,526
I promise you, I won't let him
hurt you ever again.


898
1:6:12,526 --> 1:6:21,569
I promise.


899
1:6:21,569 --> 1:6:27,508
It's not enough.
I want him stopped.


900
1:6:27,508 --> 1:6:33,481
I want the whole world
to know what he's done...


901
1:6:33,481 --> 1:6:40,2
what an evil man he is.


902
1:6:40,2 --> 1:6:41,522
